Drop -Werror from cet_set_compiler_flags.

nuevdb builds DIAGS CAUTIOUS + WERROR (inline). Under GCC 14 / C++20 (our art-stack
standard, vs upstream's C++17 default) stricter diagnostics become hard errors;
CXXFLAGS can't demote cetmodules' add_compile_options(-Werror), so drop the WERROR
keyword. See conda/potential_improvements.md (#2).
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -20,7 +20,7 @@
 include(CetCMakeEnv)
 cet_cmake_env()

-cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS CAUTIOUS WERROR
+cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS CAUTIOUS
                        NO_UNDEFINED
                        EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic
                                    -Wno-unused-local-typedefs -Wno-variadic-macros)
